  <h2>How CPC Delivers Carbon Neutral Cleaning</h2>
  <p>
    CPC operates a verified carbon offset program with documented emissions measurement methodology. Carbon neutral status is maintained through annual review of emissions measurements, ongoing reduction initiatives and verified offset procurement from accredited sources. Emissions data is made available to clients for integration into their ESG and sustainability reporting programs.
  </p>
  <p>
    Eco-certified cleaning products are integrated into CPC's standard product specifications, replacing higher-impact alternatives without compromise to cleaning performance. Energy-efficient equipment is specified as part of CPC's equipment management program, reducing the total offset requirement and demonstrating genuine emissions management.
  </p>

  <h2>Workforce and Training Model</h2>
  <p>
    CPC's environmental training covers the correct selection and dilution of eco-certified chemicals to minimise chemical waste and environmental impact, equipment energy management to reduce electricity consumption during cleaning operations, waste segregation to maximise recycling and minimise landfill, and the environmental rationale behind CPC's product and equipment choices.
  </p>
  <p>
    Environmental awareness training is integrated into standard site inductions. not delivered as a standalone module divorced from daily operations.
  </p>

  <h2>Reporting, Auditing and Evidence of Work</h2>
  <p>CPC provides clients with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Carbon neutral certification documentation and annual renewal evidence</li>
    <li>Emissions measurement methodology and annual results</li>
    <li>Eco-product registers showing certified product specifications</li>
    <li>Offset verification records confirming quality and retirement status of offsets used</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This documentation supports client ESG reporting, sustainability procurement criteria evaluation, green building certification requirements and annual sustainability committee reporting.
